  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The useless parameter passed to `miner.stop` in the 'mine only when there are transactions' trick [here](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/bitchin-tricks) - which is described as optional in [the documentation](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/JavaScript-Console#minerstop) - now appears to be mandatory:\n\n```\n> miner.stop(1)\nInvalid number of input parameters\n    at web3.js:3109:20\n    at web3.js:4922:15\n    at web3.js:4965:5\n    at web3.js:4989:23\n    at <anonymous>:1:1\n\n> miner.stop()\ntrue\n```\n",
